/*!

@page TN009 TN009 - Technical Note 009: Reflection

Vaca supports reflection of @c WM_COMMAND, @c WM_NOTIFY and @c WM_DRAWITEM
using the #Vaca::Widget methods:

- #Vaca::Widget::onCommand
- #Vaca::Widget::onNotify
- #Vaca::Widget::onDrawItem

When a widget (e.g. Vaca::Button) sends a notification
(e.g. @c BN_CLICKED) to its parent widget (e.g. Vaca::Frame), the
Frame processes the @c WM_COMMAND and extracts the handle of the button
from the @em lParam (a @c HWND). Then uses the Widget::fromHwnd
to get the @c "Button *" pointer, and finally calls Button::onCommand(...).

@see Vaca::Widget::wndProc, Vaca::Widget::fromHwnd

*/
